comments.text:
+Panneer Yuvaraja OK, so let me begin.
If your just starting out, your going to want to have a good base to build 
from. Find out how many calories you require daily to maintain current 
weight, then aim for around 10-15% surplus to bulk. If you want to lose 
weight, aim for around 10-15% deficit.
As far as BCAA's are concerned, don't worry about them too much. Just look 
for a whey protein that includes them.
As the hodgetwins referenced, Optimum Nutrition whey protein is a good 
place to start, currently what i am using and it includes BCAA's (Branched 
Chained Amino Acids) and Glutamine. 
Creatine is a good addition, but not essential at first, Just make sure you 
cycle with it. Casein Protein as far as im concerned is not really required 
for a couple reasons, adds another $100 a month to your protein bill, and 
unless your training twice a day the use of it is not warranted, all it 
does is slowly digests in your stomach, essentially it turns into a gel in 
your stomach, because sleep is the longest you usually go with out eating.
If your going to use a pre/post-work out, look for one that includes EAA's 
(Essential Amino Acids) Helps with recovery, these are the ones your body 
can NOT produce naturally. I use Amino Energy by Optimum Nutrition.

The 3 things i use in terms of supplements are:
Optimum Nutrition whey Protein.
Optimum Nutrition Amino Energy.
Axis Labs Monohydrate Creatine.

One more thing, A clean diet helps a lot.

Hope this helps dude.
comments.author: Steven Devereaux
